Use pre-built ragel 6.7 binary

This gives us few advantages:

1. No differences between Lucid and Precise.
2. No compilation problems on Windows x64 (fixed in ragel 6.7).
3. And last, but not least: -GT2 mode makes it possible to use
   one version of x86-64 validator on all platforms.

